This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it introduces a deep neural network for automated sarcasm detection that capitalizes on contextual features beyond lexical and syntactic cues present in utterances. Additionally, the paper proposes to automatically learn and exploit user embeddings, which is a common technique used in NLP. 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the analysis of social media data, which could place it in the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Sound (cs.SD), as social media data is often used in these fields for analysis and detection purposes.
